"title": "Bus Station","description": "The Dnipro Bus Station is an example of late modernism in Ukrainian architecture. In terms of design, it is the most complex bus station in all of Ukraine. The building had two levels of bus terminals, many administrative offices, and a hotel. The building was damaged by Russian shelling. Due to its young age, its architectural value is not publicly recognized, and it is unknown whether it will be restored.","subsection": "transport","location": "Дніпро / Dnipro","date_construction": "1993","date_destruction": "2023-08-24", 
"id": "obj_013.html"

