"title": "Ice Sports Palace","description": "The Severodonetsk Ice Sports Palace was one of the largest structures of its kind in the USSR, accommodating up to 5,000 spectators. The building was multifunctional: it could be used as a sports arena, a concert hall, a cinema, and a congress palace. The various functions of the building were depicted in several mosaics decorating the corners of the façade. As a result of Russian shelling, the structures supporting the roof of the hall were damaged and the building collapsed.","subsection": "sports","location": "Сєвєродонецьк / Severodonetsk","date_construction": "1970-1975","date_destruction": "2022-06-01", 
